      "writtenOn": "2020-08-07T20:56:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I looked how this is implemented in the Spanner client and I\u0027m horrified: https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-go/blob/spanner/v1.8.0/spanner/key.go#L383\n\nUsing this construction results in keySetProto() making len(batch) *recursive* calls, allocating O(len(batch)) slices and concatenating them O(len(batch)) times in a funny way: new \u003d append([]{one}, wholebunch...). This results in O(len(batch)^2) overall complexity.\n\nPlease change this to:\n\n  ks :\u003d make([]spanner.KeySet, len(batch))\n  for i,r :\u003d range batch {\n    ks[i] \u003d ...\n  }\n  \n  iter :\u003d span.Read(..., spanner.KeySets(ks...), ...)\n\nIt at least will be O(N).",
